he README examples use com.openai.client.okhttp.OpenAIOkHttpClient, and the published aggregate com.openai:openai-java depends on this artifact. The target core artifact alone does not provide the concrete OkHttp client used for normal client construction.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not call the live OpenAI service. If exercising client/service request paths, use a dummy API key and point the client at a local/fake endpoint, or use core model/JSON serialization APIs directly. Avoid requiring real OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_BASE_URL, Azure credentials, or network access.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding the OkHttp client broadens the test classpath beyond the requested core artifact, so tests should keep assertions focused on core OpenAI request/model behavior.\",\n    \"Live API examples in the documentation require credentials and network access; generated tests must avoid those paths.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fbcb4535d9be058016a3f19dd4c648197b3f317ba4009be66\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1221, "output": 1343, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31748, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782520267074, "responseId": "resp_0fbcb4535d9be058016a3f19cb91e881978b379d7d819b7f00"}}
